name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: .@nevadadot and @NV_StatePolice are reporting wet roads and dropping temperatures that could result in dangerous conditions in the Carson, Washoe, and Douglas.      As such, I have ordered an early closing for all state offices in these areas effective immediately. Drive safely!

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: Take it from our public health experts:   "The best course of action is to be vaccinated and boosted."

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: Attention, woman, veteran, and minority small business owners: grant applications are now open for six-months of rent, utilities and more in newly renovated incubator Launchpad by @hcc_nevada! Deadline 1-31-22. Apply at  https://t.co/XAgHA3xbRz.  https://t.co/RzIyPyzY97

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: I look forward to speaking to @jaketapper on @CNN about the life and legacy of @SenatorReid. Please tune in soon.

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: I’ve often said through this pandemic that safety is a partnership.   Thank you to the @NevadaGCB for this reminder and for your continued efforts.

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: Today, I issued an executive order to address the growth in cost of healthcare in Nevada.    This executive order helps ensure that healthcare costs do no grow unchecked and create undue hardship for patients.  https://t.co/P4QlRO7McH

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: This morning, I was honored to join @CBSNews by phone to talk about @SenatorReid and the legacy he is leaving on the State of Nevada. Thank you, @BLBlackburn, for having me on.  You can watch the segment here:  https://t.co/tHOQuBK7Rw

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: Nevada is awarding $30M in grant funds for community behavioral health providers. DHHS is accepting applications for organizations, agencies, private practices, tribes, non-profits, and more. The deadline to apply is Jan. 31, 2022.   To learn more, visit:  https://t.co/s2KlVxprH9

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: The State is committed to continuing the regulatory process with the Board of Health as it relates to proof of vaccination requirements for students.   By working together, we can all do our part to help protect our communities & ensure students & staff are able to learn & thrive

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: We know without a doubt that COVID-19 vaccines help prevent severe cases, hospitalization, & death from this virus. I want to thank all the NSHE employees & students who have already rolled up their sleeves to give themselves with additional layer of protection from COVID-19.

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: The Regents are empowered under Nevada’s Constitution and laws to take such measures and I support their efforts to create safer and healthier communities for all our students, staff and faculty.

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: I encourage the @nshe Board of Regents to continue with the policy they enacted earlier this year to require proof of vaccination for employees - we know these measures work in helping to prevent the further spread of the virus.  https://t.co/FWgtHJMe06

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: I’ve signed an executive order to lower flags in the State of Nevada in honor of @SenatorReid. The fully executed order is forthcoming.  https://t.co/swEXVI8b3T

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: With federal loans paid & employer contributions coming in, the UI Trust Fund has a healthy $316 million. The Trust Fund can now cover a normal year’s worth of benefit payments, putting us in a good fiscal spot as we head into 2022 with a focus on the economy.

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: I want to thank all of our first responders and emergency officials who worked diligently through challenging conditions overnight (and for most of the last week) to ensure our roadways and motorists are safe.   Thank you!   (@NV_StatePolice, @nevadadot, @NVEmergencyMgmt)

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: I look forward to calling into @CBSNews and talking to @BLBlackburn about the life and legacy of Nevada’s @SenatorReid. Please tune in around 6:10 a.m.     https://t.co/GDe8TNW7vK

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: UPDATE:  A warming shelter is now open at the Douglas County Community & Senior Center at 1329 Waterloo Lane in Gardnerville. Please help share this message to those who may need a place to stop in. I am appreciative of the strong collaboration between State & local partners.

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: I want to thank our emergency responders for working diligently through trying weather conditions to keep our roadways and travelers safe. We need all those who are on the roadways to turn around and head back to safe shelter so our emergency responders can continue their work.

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: The Emergency will allow officials to order cars to head back into the valley until conditions subside and the roadways are safe. This will help prevent motorists from becoming stranded, potentially running out of gas in subfreezing temperatures without emergency services.

name: Governor Sisolak
tweet: State officials, including the @nevadadot, @NVEmergencyMgmt  and @NV_StatePolice  need to be able to clear roadways to make room for emergency vehicles and snow removal.
